Unreleased
	* SemiBin: Drop support for Python 3.8 (minimum is now Python 3.9)
	* SemiBin: Drop support for Python 3.9 (minimum is now Python 3.10)
	* SemiBin: Use zip(..., strict=True) for paired-array iterations
	  to catch silent length-mismatch bugs in clustering, marker
	  handling, and feature generation
	* single_easy_bin: Fix TypeError when combining '--environment'
	  with abundance files ('-a') instead of BAM files; the
	  unsupported combination is now rejected cleanly
	* GTDB download: Include the underlying error message when
	  extracting the GTDB tarball fails, instead of a generic
	  'cannot untar the file'
	* SemiBin: Fix several broken/garbled error messages (a missing
	  space merged two sentences in check_install; the
	  '--train-from-many' shape-mismatch message was unreadable; the
	  pretrained-model message now reads 'can only be used for')
	* SemiBin: Route fatal error messages through the logger instead
	  of writing directly to stderr, so they are timestamped and
	  recorded in SemiBinRun.log; also drop the redundant 'Error:'
	  prefix and trailing newline from logged errors

Version 2.3.0 May 26 2026 by BigDataBiology
	* SemiBin1: removed
	* SemiBin: Accept 'hybrid' as a synonym for 'long_read' in --sequencing-type (#216)
	* SemiBin: Remove '--environment' parameter in command that learns a new model (#218)
	* single_easy_bin: Fix AttributeError on 'training_type' when running
	  with abundance files (-a) instead of BAM files
	* semi-supervised: Fix wrong input in unlabeled contrastive learning
	  (both branches received identical data, defeating the unlabeled-pair
	  contrastive signal)
	* long-read clustering: Clip zero depth values before np.log
	  (previously produced -inf values that silently corrupted the embedding)
	* utils: Fix split_data matching sample names that are prefixes of others
	  (use str.startswith() instead of str.contains())
	* markers: Validate cached markers.hmmout against input fingerprint
	  (FASTA size/mtime, binned_length, ORF finder) to avoid silently
	  reusing stale marker calls when reruns target an existing output dir
	* long-read binning: Remove stale output bins from previous runs before
	  writing new results
	* SemiBin: Empty FASTA inputs now fail cleanly with a user-facing error
	  instead of crashing with ZeroDivisionError / argmax-on-empty
	* orffinding: Fix prodigal errors being silently ignored
	* model_load: Raise ValueError for unknown model name (instead of
	  UnboundLocalError)
	* check_install: Fix logic when checking for prodigal
	* check_install: Soft-check for samtools (warns when missing in verbose
	  mode but does not fail; samtools is only required for CRAM input)
	* SemiBin: Mark --allow-missing-mmseqs2 as deprecated in help text
	* SemiBin: Update data-generation log message to distinguish training
	  from inference with a pretrained model (#219)
	* self-supervised: Read training CSVs once instead of every epoch
	* orffinding: Fix unclosed file handle in run_prodigal
	* pyproject: Remove unused pyyaml dependency
	* Add Python 3.14 to the tested Python versions
	* Add missing COPYING.MIT license file (#214)
	* docs: Fix multiple documentation issues (outdated output descriptions,
	  wrong split_contigs output filename, removed CLI option references,
	  inaccurate required arguments, installation inconsistencies, broken
	  links, Python version ranges, --random-seed help text, CITATION DOI,
	  --depth-metabat2 mention on subcommand without that option, etc.)

